setDefaultReadLibConfigs((uint32,(addres.details: about the DEFAULT ReadLib config 1) its values are all LITERAL (e.g. 0 is 0). whereas in the oapp ReadLib config, 0 (default value) points to the default ReadLib config     this design enables the oapp to point to DEFAULT config without explicitly setting the config 2) its configuration is more restrictive than the oapp ReadLib config that     a) it must not use NIL value, where NIL is used only by oapps to indicate the LITERAL 0     b) it must have at least one DVN and executor

documentation.text:
@dev about the DEFAULT ReadLib config
 1) its values are all LITERAL (e.g. 0 is 0). whereas in the oapp ReadLib config, 0 (default value) points to the default ReadLib config
     this design enables the oapp to point to DEFAULT config without explicitly setting the config
 2) its configuration is more restrictive than the oapp ReadLib config that
     a) it must not use NIL value, where NIL is used only by oapps to indicate the LITERAL 0
     b) it must have at least one DVN and executor
